summary: This document is an email chain from January 19, 2021, regarding an interview with a witness's attorney. The attorney provides a proffer stating her client did not observe anything inappropriate or illegal around Jeffrey Epstein but recalls a person named from a well-known Swedish family. The email is from an Assistant United States Attorney in the Southern District of New York.

persons.name: Jeffrey Epstein
persons.context: Mentioned as the central figure around whom the witness's observations and memories are being discussed in relation to young women or girls.

events.title: Attorney call regarding witness interview
events.description: A call occurred between an Assistant U.S. Attorney and an attorney representing a witness to discuss logistics and topics for an upcoming interview. The attorney provided a proffer about her client's observations.

locations: One Saint Andrew's Plaza, New York, NY 10007
keyFacts: An attorney proffered that her client did not observe anything inappropriate or illegal around Jeffrey Epstein at the time.
The witness recalled someone named from a well-known family in Sweden.
The prosecutor was planning to ask the witness about awareness of young women or girls around Epstein.
The correspondence is dated January 19, 2021, from an Assistant U.S. Attorney in the Southern District of New York.
